ZigzagDownLoader (ZDL)
**********************

_ZigzagDownLoader_ is a download manager:
   - equipped with command line user interfaces (_CLI_), for terminals
     (_TUI_), graphics (_GUI_) and for internet and web applications
     (_Web-UI_);

   - handles downloads of some downloaders such as _Aria2_, _Axel_,
     _Wget_, _RTMPDump_ or _cURL_, using its potential (for example,
     download acceleration);

   - extracts the URL of the files to be downloaded from file hosting
     and video streaming services, also using `youtube-dl' extensions
     (or _extractors_);

   - downloads _TORRENT_;

   - automatically requests and downloads files via _IRC/XDCC_, without
     any human interaction via chat;

   - downloads movies _LIVE_ from some television networks

   - extends web browsers, such as _Conkeror_, _XXXTerm/Xombrero_ and,
     using _Flashgot_, _Firefox_;

   - the _External Application Button_ extension integrates ZDL into
     _Firefox_, _Chrome/Chromium_ and _Opera_;

   - using _Cygwin_, it also works in _Microsoft Windows_ (CLI and TUI
     interfaces, also from _Firefox_ + _Flashgot_ of Windows).

   The server and web interfaces, for remote and network control, make
it a useful tool for a _Network Attached Storage_ (_NAS_). The
interfaces are _responsive_ and suitable for different devices. In
particular, they can also be used as a remote control for launching
multimedia files already downloaded or being downloaded, using a web
browser on mobile devices.

   Furthermore, the Web interfaces (_Web-UI_) and graphics (_GUI_)
allow the quick and intuitive search and selection of _files via XDCC_,
without having to perform any IRC/chat.  All interfaces allow _live-tv_
recordings to be programmed.

   But ZDL is also much more, because it can be:
   - combined with other programs or inserted into a script, as a work
     tool

   - extended by the user, who can develop new extensions suitable for
     their purposes

   - a polyglot system, using different interpreters (for PHP,
     Javascript, Python, Perl, Awk ...) and Bash tools

   ZigzagDownLoader is a "zigzag" program: it is not just a program, it
is a laboratory and a system open to new inventions.

