Stop mode
*********

ZDL can be stopped in different ways:
   * If the downloads are managed by the "non-interactive"/standard
     mode:

       1. typing `M-k' (in this case all downloads started by ZDL in
          the specified destination directory or in the current one
          will be interrupted)

       2. typing `M-q' (all downloads already started in the current
          directory will not be interrupted, but will no longer be
          managed by ZDL until a new _standard_ or _daemon_ instance of
          the program)

   * If the downloads are managed by the "daemon" mode: through the
     interactive mode `zdl -i' started in the directory managed by the
     daemon, by typing the "Quit" exit key (capitalized, that is, with
     `Shift-q'): `Q' (in this case the downloads started in the
     directory will not be interrupted, but will not be managed by ZDL
     unless it is restarted to manage the same downloads)


