Torrent
*******

Aria2 allows the download of _torrents_. This downloader does not have
to be explicitly indicated to ZDL, but it must be installed correctly.
A _torrent_ can be started by simply sending the _URL magnet_ (through
all the systems provided for URLs in general, ZDL recognizes the
_magnet_ automatically) or by sending the _file torrent_, using the
`--torrent-file=' option or the file marked with the _.torrent_
extension.
The _TCP_ and _UDP_ ports can be set in the ZDL configuration (with the
command `zdl --configure' or in the file `$ HOME/.zdl/zdl.conf'),
explicitly indicated with the options `--tcp-port=' and `--udp-port='
or indicated in the _Aria2_ configuration. It is important that the
ports are opened by the router.


